WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.041 --> 00:00:09.458
Don't fear pain.

2
00:00:09.541 --> 00:00:13.208
fear the part of you
too weak to survive it.

3
00:00:15.416 --> 00:00:19.875
When Argosax's forces came.
you flailed like prey.

4
00:00:23.625 --> 00:00:27.250
I will make you a shadow
that kills without mercy.

5
00:00:33.416 --> 00:00:36.000
Emotion is a disease.

6
00:00:36.083 --> 00:00:40.583
Mock it. erase it.
dominate those who suffer from it.

7
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:48.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

8
00:00:58.416 --> 00:01:01.708
[Mundus] The battlefield
punishes sentiment.

9
00:01:12.750 --> 00:01:15.750
Your power is hereditary.

10
00:01:15.833 --> 00:01:18.208
Your right by bloodline.

11
00:01:20.375 --> 00:01:23.000
Are you strong enough to claim it?

12
00:01:33.416 --> 00:01:35.833
[Vergil] He bore the mark of Argosax.

13
00:01:37.458 --> 00:01:42.416
[Mundus] Tell me. heir of Sparda.
what sentence does treason earn?

14
00:01:43.250 --> 00:01:45.291
[Vergil] <i>What always happens</i>
<i>to the infected.</i>

15
00:01:47.166 --> 00:01:49.041
<i>Mercy's how their virus spreads.</i>

16
00:01:56.875 --> 00:02:00.833
[Mundus] Hope is cowardice
dressed as virtue.

17
00:02:00.916 --> 00:02:05.250
Your mother knew an attack was coming.
and waited like a lamb.

18
00:02:06.583 --> 00:02:08.500
She believed goodness was enough.

19
00:02:09.250 --> 00:02:11.791
[Mundus] Then goodness killed her.

20
00:02:19.583 --> 00:02:21.583
[somber. emotional music playing]

21
00:02:23.166 --> 00:02:24.666
[Vergil whimpering]

22
00:02:34.541 --> 00:02:36.958
[Mundus] Devils don't cry. Vergil.

23
00:02:38.333 --> 00:02:40.208
Then I'll kill the boy who did.

24
00:02:42.041 --> 00:02:45.750
[Mundus] Argosax made a game
of cruel emotion.

25
00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:51.833
He'd force mothers to watch
while he fed on their children.

26
00:02:52.333 --> 00:02:54.750
He laughed as they screamed.

27
00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:59.416
I was the one who finally ended him.

28
00:03:03.875 --> 00:03:07.000
But only because I was strong enough.

29
00:03:08.958 --> 00:03:11.958
Weakness dies screaming.

30
00:03:28.083 --> 00:03:28.916
[distorted clanging]

31
00:03:34.250 --> 00:03:38.250
And you thought you could
just walk in and take the chalice.

32
00:03:38.333 --> 00:03:42.083
Might prove somewhat difficult.
now that I absorbed it.

33
00:03:42.916 --> 00:03:44.083
Perfect.

34
00:03:44.166 --> 00:03:47.583
This way I can take the Arcana
and kill you in one go.

35
00:03:48.583 --> 00:03:49.708
Of course.

36
00:03:51.750 --> 00:03:53.541
[aggressive metal music playing]

37
00:04:04.541 --> 00:04:07.875
So you deny you played
any role in the attack on my home?

38
00:04:08.583 --> 00:04:13.333
You gave aid to the animals
who tortured me and killed my mother!

39
00:04:16.208 --> 00:04:17.333
It's the truth.

40
00:04:25.333 --> 00:04:28.041
You could have asked them
who they were aided by.

41
00:04:28.125 --> 00:04:32.041
had Mundus not generously
offered them up for you to kill.

42
00:04:32.125 --> 00:04:34.541
without any chance for interrogation.

43
00:04:35.041 --> 00:04:37.916
If you know that much. Mundus was right.

44
00:04:38.750 --> 00:04:40.666
There is a traitor.

45
00:04:40.750 --> 00:04:44.291
One ideally placed
at the highest levels of his court.

46
00:04:44.375 --> 00:04:47.375
and yet still invisible to you all.

47
00:04:50.750 --> 00:04:52.833
[operatic choral chanting]

48
00:05:06.750 --> 00:05:10.791
I am beyond human limitation.

49
00:05:47.833 --> 00:05:51.375
Poetic. if a bit on the nose.

50
00:05:51.458 --> 00:05:53.166
Held by my will.

51
00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:57.583
like you have been since the moment
my messenger reached you in Makai.

52
00:06:01.416 --> 00:06:03.833
He's dying to meet you.

53
00:06:05.166 --> 00:06:07.208
A dangling marionette.

54
00:06:07.291 --> 00:06:11.875
Your stolen source of power will gain you
nothing but cheap tricks without the--

55
00:06:11.958 --> 00:06:14.208
[Arius] The other three Arcana.

56
00:06:14.291 --> 00:06:16.750
Yes. I already have them.

57
00:06:21.541 --> 00:06:23.583
You were right on one count.

58
00:06:23.666 --> 00:06:26.666
I did adopt the Uroboros in tribute.

59
00:06:26.750 --> 00:06:32.750
I have everything I need now
to restore to Makai its true ruler.

60
00:06:34.041 --> 00:06:37.416
<i>Argosax the Chaos.</i>

61
00:06:43.291 --> 00:06:45.291
[rowdy rock music intro playing]

62
00:07:09.083 --> 00:07:10.083
[music trails off]

63
00:07:13.291 --> 00:07:15.291
[grim. foreboding music playing]

64
00:07:35.875 --> 00:07:36.875
[Dante coughs]

65
00:07:37.875 --> 00:07:42.083
[weakly] Hey. I was using that
to keep my organs in.

66
00:07:42.166 --> 00:07:43.333
I'm sorry.

67
00:07:44.041 --> 00:07:46.375
I'm sorry about everything.

68
00:07:50.541 --> 00:07:52.583
[Dante] You're apologizing?

69
00:07:52.666 --> 00:07:53.958
What's wrong?

70
00:07:56.666 --> 00:07:59.208
The White Rabbit. I had met him before.

71
00:07:59.291 --> 00:08:00.291
<i>As a human.</i>

72
00:08:01.125 --> 00:08:03.791
<i>We turned him into what he became.</i>

73
00:08:05.708 --> 00:08:09.000
<i>then lied to the world about it</i>
<i>so we could invade Makai.</i>

74
00:08:11.958 --> 00:08:13.250
Why'd you stay then?

75
00:08:13.333 --> 00:08:16.583
All I know how to do is slaughter demons.

76
00:08:16.666 --> 00:08:19.375
It's the only stability
I've had in my life.

77
00:08:19.458 --> 00:08:22.291
<i>I'm terrified of change.</i>

78
00:08:23.916 --> 00:08:26.375
<i>But today. I found out</i>

79
00:08:27.541 --> 00:08:31.541
Baines executed those families
in the White Rabbit's building.

80
00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:33.458
Children.

81
00:08:34.041 --> 00:08:36.083
The ones I tried to save.

82
00:08:36.666 --> 00:08:39.458
Lady. you tried.

83
00:08:39.541 --> 00:08:42.791
I failed. and I'm a fucking liar.

84
00:08:42.875 --> 00:08:44.041
Wha…

85
00:08:45.541 --> 00:08:46.458
Wait.

86
00:08:47.833 --> 00:08:50.291
I need your help to get Vergil back.

87
00:08:50.375 --> 00:08:51.250
[Lady] Still?

88
00:08:51.333 --> 00:08:53.166
He just tried to kill you.

89
00:08:53.875 --> 00:08:55.916
If we'd been trying to kill each other.

90
00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:59.583
we would have destroyed a lot more
than a couple flimsy buildings.

91
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:03.666
I can't just abandon him.

92
00:09:03.750 --> 00:09:04.750
Not again.

93
00:09:08.750 --> 00:09:09.791
Okay.

94
00:09:09.875 --> 00:09:11.291
I'll take you to him.

95
00:09:11.875 --> 00:09:14.250
Really? Just like that?

96
00:09:14.750 --> 00:09:17.208
You don't want to have
an armed standoff about it?

97
00:09:18.291 --> 00:09:20.041
I owe you this.

98
00:09:21.416 --> 00:09:23.125
[distant rumbling]

99
00:09:31.875 --> 00:09:36.083
You think a sapien like you
can simply resurrect Argosax?

100
00:09:37.125 --> 00:09:40.458
And people call me pretentious?

101
00:09:40.541 --> 00:09:43.333
You're still making
melodramatic pronouncements

102
00:09:43.416 --> 00:09:46.291
when you're a single stroke
away from death.

103
00:09:46.375 --> 00:09:49.583
Almost a shame
you're of more use to me alive.

104
00:09:51.125 --> 00:09:52.500
Or you will be.

105
00:09:52.583 --> 00:09:56.000
Once you finally see
Mundus for what he is.

106
00:09:56.083 --> 00:10:01.375
All of Makai has had its potential
strangled by his unbending hierarchy.

107
00:10:02.291 --> 00:10:07.583
Just like this realm has been crippled
by the rule of bloated. myopic cowards.

108
00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:11.500
But only for 22 hours longer.

109
00:10:13.708 --> 00:10:16.500
Chaos is freedom.

110
00:10:16.583 --> 00:10:19.875
Argosax will break the chains on us all.

111
00:10:19.958 --> 00:10:22.458
[Dante] Hey. Mr. Magic Man.

112
00:10:22.541 --> 00:10:24.208
[rowdy rock music playing]

113
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:28.291
Been meaning to tell ya.
You got a little something.

114
00:10:29.291 --> 00:10:30.166
Right here.

115
00:10:44.833 --> 00:10:46.583
That's one arm unchained.

116
00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:10.208
Vergil!

117
00:11:12.375 --> 00:11:15.875
What the fuck? I was gone five minutes!

118
00:11:26.250 --> 00:11:27.750
[Arius groaning]

119
00:11:39.208 --> 00:11:40.958
[Arius groaning]

120
00:11:43.875 --> 00:11:46.708
The pain doesn't deter you. does it. sir?

121
00:11:49.833 --> 00:11:52.375
My father put me through worse.

122
00:12:01.583 --> 00:12:02.500
[in Italian] Dad!

123
00:12:03.500 --> 00:12:04.375
Dad!

124
00:12:04.458 --> 00:12:05.958
Maybe I can help.

125
00:12:06.458 --> 00:12:07.458
[cries out]

126
00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:17.958
Help? You're the problem.

127
00:12:20.333 --> 00:12:22.000
{\an8}With just one of the Arcana.

128
00:12:22.083 --> 00:12:24.583
{\an8}I was able to best that son of Sparda.

129
00:12:25.250 --> 00:12:30.458
Let's see those gold-plated cultists
at Fortuna try and buy that!

130
00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:42.833
Vergil!

131
00:12:44.458 --> 00:12:46.166
What the hell is happening?

132
00:12:48.291 --> 00:12:51.083
When did he get magic fucking powers?

133
00:12:51.166 --> 00:12:52.583
Where are we?

134
00:12:53.166 --> 00:12:54.916
[Vergil] Do not interfere.

135
00:12:55.541 --> 00:12:59.208
Or else in 22 hours.
your master ends both our worlds.

136
00:12:59.291 --> 00:13:00.916
What are you talking about?

137
00:13:01.916 --> 00:13:03.166
The Arcana.

138
00:13:03.250 --> 00:13:05.708
You have no idea
what you've helped bring about

139
00:13:05.791 --> 00:13:08.458
by putting them in Arius' hands. do you?

140
00:13:08.541 --> 00:13:11.875
He said they're a stealth weapon
that can take out your genocidal king.

141
00:13:12.458 --> 00:13:15.291
A clever lie. I'll give him that.

142
00:13:15.375 --> 00:13:19.666
The Arcana are relics of ancient power.
as old as existence itself.

143
00:13:19.750 --> 00:13:23.958
Arius means to use them
to raise the God of Chaos. Argosax.

144
00:13:24.041 --> 00:13:26.750
[scoffs] Is that more Mundus propaganda?

145
00:13:27.375 --> 00:13:29.333
I saw you arrive in the bunker.

146
00:13:29.416 --> 00:13:32.041
You heard it from Arius' own lips.

147
00:13:32.125 --> 00:13:34.708
Argosax was the scourge of Makai.

148
00:13:34.791 --> 00:13:37.916
a sadistic overlord vanquished by Mundus.

149
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:41.791
Their sapien image of hell.
fire and torment.

150
00:13:41.875 --> 00:13:45.375
came from glimpses of Makai
under Argosax's rule.

151
00:13:46.625 --> 00:13:50.125
And you're saying
that Arius wants to bring him back?

152
00:13:50.208 --> 00:13:51.458
Yes.

153
00:13:51.541 --> 00:13:53.291
To not only destroy Mundus.

154
00:13:53.375 --> 00:13:56.666
but purge both realms
in the flames of Chaos.

155
00:13:58.916 --> 00:14:01.916
If it's really all about Chaos Guy
and these Arcana things.

156
00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.833
what was Arius draining your blood for?

157
00:14:03.916 --> 00:14:06.083
To open the rift with Makai.

158
00:14:06.166 --> 00:14:09.333
He said it would give us
a clear shot at Mundus.

159
00:14:10.083 --> 00:14:11.541
Seriously?

160
00:14:11.625 --> 00:14:14.166
After everything we went through
keeping the rift closed.

161
00:14:14.250 --> 00:14:16.958
- you were just going to open it anyway?
- Temporarily.

162
00:14:17.041 --> 00:14:18.791
[restrained seething]

163
00:14:20.500 --> 00:14:21.958
I lied to you.

164
00:14:22.791 --> 00:14:24.000
I'm a piece of shit.

165
00:14:24.833 --> 00:14:25.833
Ha.

166
00:14:25.916 --> 00:14:28.333
Now you see. I was right.

167
00:14:28.416 --> 00:14:31.750
You were the one trying to use the Rabbit
to open the rift in the first place!

168
00:14:31.833 --> 00:14:32.958
On Mundus' orders!

169
00:14:34.291 --> 00:14:37.416
Our father's barrier
is no longer necessary.

170
00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:41.875
Contrary to the sapiens' story.
he never raised it to protect humans.

171
00:14:41.958 --> 00:14:45.208
but to keep Makai pure from contamination.

172
00:14:46.250 --> 00:14:48.583
Dad didn't see humans that way.

173
00:14:48.666 --> 00:14:50.708
Why would he be with Mom if he did?

174
00:14:50.791 --> 00:14:53.291
You think he meant
to sire his heirs with her?

175
00:14:53.375 --> 00:14:57.833
That there is any mystery
why we never knew him? It's obvious.

176
00:14:57.916 --> 00:15:02.000
He was as ashamed of
his paramour's nature as you should be.

177
00:15:02.083 --> 00:15:04.583
Is that really how you feel about her?

178
00:15:04.666 --> 00:15:06.083
[seethes]

179
00:15:06.875 --> 00:15:08.041
{\an8}[tracker beeping]

180
00:15:14.041 --> 00:15:16.041
My tracker has a lock on the Arcana.

181
00:15:16.125 --> 00:15:17.458
All four.

182
00:15:17.541 --> 00:15:20.541
The chalice must still be
with Arius upstairs.

183
00:15:20.625 --> 00:15:22.458
But the other three are here too.

184
00:15:22.541 --> 00:15:24.083
Somewhere in this basement.

185
00:15:24.166 --> 00:15:27.708
You said we've got 22 hours
before this happens. right?

186
00:15:27.791 --> 00:15:29.208
Why would Arius wait?

187
00:15:29.291 --> 00:15:30.708
The eclipse.

188
00:15:30.791 --> 00:15:33.083
There's a hybrid solar eclipse tomorrow.

189
00:15:33.166 --> 00:15:35.375
It happens once every century and a half.

190
00:15:35.458 --> 00:15:36.541
Yes.

191
00:15:37.125 --> 00:15:41.125
The cosmic energy would allow Arius
to fully activate the Arcana.

192
00:15:41.208 --> 00:15:43.625
But only if he has all four.

193
00:15:43.708 --> 00:15:45.416
At least one Arcana must be taken

194
00:15:45.500 --> 00:15:48.250
and kept from him
until the eclipse is over.

195
00:15:49.416 --> 00:15:51.166
So. we have a plan then.

196
00:15:51.250 --> 00:15:53.250
I'll take us to the Arcana.

197
00:15:54.083 --> 00:15:57.583
if you two can keep
from impaling each other long enough.

198
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:00.666
Mmm.

199
00:16:16.458 --> 00:16:20.458
[in Italian] Quit looking up there.
you tiny idiot.

200
00:16:22.833 --> 00:16:27.458
God's condemned us all to suffer.

201
00:16:28.041 --> 00:16:32.833
We are but a speck
on the shit that is this world.

202
00:16:32.916 --> 00:16:39.375
And there is nothing you or I
can do about it.

203
00:16:48.833 --> 00:16:49.666
Signal lost.

204
00:16:50.833 --> 00:16:54.208
Sir. there appears to be
a glitch with the security matrix.

205
00:16:54.291 --> 00:16:56.500
No. not a glitch.

206
00:17:06.291 --> 00:17:09.791
Ugh. our empowered. liberated Lady.

207
00:17:09.875 --> 00:17:12.333
Arkham couldn't have gotten here alone.

208
00:17:12.416 --> 00:17:14.875
The brothers Sparda must be with her.

209
00:17:14.958 --> 00:17:17.958
Shall I activate the failed experiments
from the prison?

210
00:17:18.041 --> 00:17:19.583
<i>They may still be useful.</i>

211
00:17:19.666 --> 00:17:22.541
{\an8}Go. I'll meet you there.

212
00:17:24.541 --> 00:17:27.333
[frantic tapping]

213
00:17:29.583 --> 00:17:31.583
[groaning softly]

214
00:17:32.250 --> 00:17:35.166
Any word yet on Arius or Baines?

215
00:17:35.666 --> 00:17:37.166
[indistinct radio chatter]

216
00:17:37.250 --> 00:17:39.083
Sir. their bunker caved in.

217
00:17:39.166 --> 00:17:40.541
No sign of survivors.

218
00:17:41.208 --> 00:17:42.958
Well. that's a damn shame.

219
00:17:43.625 --> 00:17:46.041
They'll be mourned as heroes.

220
00:17:52.125 --> 00:17:54.291
All right.

221
00:17:54.375 --> 00:17:56.666
Let's get me ready
for my big announcement.

222
00:17:56.750 --> 00:17:59.375
- Think I'll break out the new Stetson.
- [door opens]

223
00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:03.166
[gasping]

224
00:18:10.750 --> 00:18:11.833
[Hopper] Bainesie!

225
00:18:11.916 --> 00:18:13.000
Jed.

226
00:18:13.083 --> 00:18:13.916
You…

227
00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:15.500
You got out.

228
00:18:15.583 --> 00:18:16.541
Praise the Lord.

229
00:18:16.625 --> 00:18:17.875
[Baines] Indeed.

230
00:18:17.958 --> 00:18:21.791
{\an8}Though it seems
you now serve a different master.

231
00:18:22.375 --> 00:18:25.166
What are you yammering on about?

232
00:18:26.541 --> 00:18:28.708
What… What is all this?

233
00:18:29.458 --> 00:18:30.750
<i>Gentlemen.</i>

234
00:18:31.416 --> 00:18:34.166
You'll have to forgive
my divided attention.

235
00:18:34.250 --> 00:18:37.166
There isn't enough of me
to go around these days.

236
00:18:37.250 --> 00:18:41.375
I regret to inform you all
that your president is a traitor.

237
00:18:41.458 --> 00:18:42.625
Now hold on!

238
00:18:42.708 --> 00:18:44.500
What kind of wild accusation?

239
00:18:44.583 --> 00:18:46.125
This is treason!

240
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:47.291
Arrest them!

241
00:18:47.375 --> 00:18:49.583
Arrest them all!

242
00:18:49.666 --> 00:18:52.041
<i>We. of course. have evidence.</i>

243
00:18:55.083 --> 00:19:00.375
<i>I can promise your king</i>
<i>a full withdrawal of all US troops.</i>

244
00:19:00.458 --> 00:19:02.041
[Vergil] <i>And in exchange?</i>

245
00:19:02.125 --> 00:19:06.750
[Hopper] <i>Well. I will need</i>
<i>Mundus to concede publicly.</i>

246
00:19:06.833 --> 00:19:08.625
<i>but that's just for show.</i>

247
00:19:08.708 --> 00:19:10.791
<i>Election year. you understand.</i>

248
00:19:11.750 --> 00:19:16.041
<i>As a show of good faith.</i>
<i>I'm going to give you something up front.</i>

249
00:19:17.166 --> 00:19:19.375
<i>- The Arcana's location.</i>
- [gasping]

250
00:19:20.125 --> 00:19:22.250
I canvassed for you.

251
00:19:22.333 --> 00:19:24.791
I am the goddamn president!

252
00:19:24.875 --> 00:19:30.000
It's my prerogative to negotiate
with our adversaries as I see fit!

253
00:19:30.583 --> 00:19:34.791
And to sacrifice your own people
in a covenant with Satan.

254
00:19:34.875 --> 00:19:38.750
You're the one who went
and picked a goddamn fight with him!

255
00:19:38.833 --> 00:19:43.375
And you were more than happy
for a cause to rally the country behind.

256
00:19:43.458 --> 00:19:45.625
<i>William. we're on the clock.</i>

257
00:19:47.916 --> 00:19:50.666
Take President Hopper into custody.

258
00:19:51.416 --> 00:19:53.708
Y'all really think you can pin this on me?

259
00:19:53.791 --> 00:19:56.750
Why don't you go ahead and play
the rest of the tape for 'em. huh?

260
00:19:56.833 --> 00:19:59.625
You wanna know
what else the half-demon told me?

261
00:19:59.708 --> 00:20:04.333
That the terrorist they convinced me
to go to war over. the White Rabbit?

262
00:20:05.375 --> 00:20:07.625
It wasn't even a fucking demon!

263
00:20:07.708 --> 00:20:10.708
He was a human in a goddamn bunny suit!

264
00:20:10.791 --> 00:20:12.833
They lied to me. they lied to all of us!

265
00:20:27.416 --> 00:20:29.166
[DARKCOM agent whimpering]

266
00:20:33.083 --> 00:20:34.541
I fucked up.

267
00:20:37.333 --> 00:20:41.333
<i>Well. that streamlines our solution…</i>

268
00:20:41.416 --> 00:20:42.958
<i>Mr. President.</i>

269
00:20:48.125 --> 00:20:49.583
[DARKCOM agent] I fucked up.

270
00:20:53.041 --> 00:20:55.583
[Lady] So if Argosax is Mundus' archenemy.

271
00:20:55.666 --> 00:20:58.458
why did Mundus have
one of the things that can resurrect him

272
00:20:58.541 --> 00:21:00.375
just hanging around his castle?

273
00:21:00.458 --> 00:21:02.375
Why not destroy it?

274
00:21:02.458 --> 00:21:06.208
The Arcana's energy
is connected to Makai itself.

275
00:21:06.291 --> 00:21:08.458
It can't be destroyed within Makai.

276
00:21:09.041 --> 00:21:11.583
Theoretically. it could be done
in the Earth realm.

277
00:21:11.666 --> 00:21:14.625
but there's no one alive
who could channel enough power.

278
00:21:14.708 --> 00:21:16.333
I might know a guy.

279
00:21:16.416 --> 00:21:18.375
Foolishness. Dante.

280
00:21:18.458 --> 00:21:20.375
It must be kept hidden.

281
00:21:21.875 --> 00:21:23.000
[Lady] Through here.

282
00:21:28.458 --> 00:21:29.833
[alarm blares]

283
00:21:32.458 --> 00:21:33.541
[Vergil] Stand aside.

284
00:21:36.125 --> 00:21:37.041
[gunshot]

285
00:21:45.333 --> 00:21:46.583
Let's go.

286
00:21:47.208 --> 00:21:48.875
- Hm.
- [grumbles]

287
00:21:59.708 --> 00:22:00.958
[Dante] Oooh.

288
00:22:06.708 --> 00:22:07.875
Kinda like old times.

289
00:22:07.958 --> 00:22:10.375
playing hide-and-seek
with the neighborhood kids.

290
00:22:10.458 --> 00:22:11.416
Hmm?

291
00:22:15.041 --> 00:22:16.291
Hm.

292
00:22:16.375 --> 00:22:19.541
Those are offerings of worship
to Argosax from when he reigned.

293
00:22:20.041 --> 00:22:21.333
They're worthless.

294
00:22:22.625 --> 00:22:25.375
Hm. [jaunty whistling]

295
00:22:31.875 --> 00:22:33.375
[eerie music playing]

296
00:22:45.166 --> 00:22:48.833
Look at us. Arkham.

297
00:22:50.333 --> 00:22:54.750
Just a pair of sapiens
who've been playing make believe.

298
00:22:56.625 --> 00:22:59.333
At least now you see yourself

299
00:22:59.416 --> 00:23:00.666
for what you are.

300
00:23:01.666 --> 00:23:05.833
A blood-soaked murderer
in service of a horrifying cause

301
00:23:05.916 --> 00:23:09.416
to which you've remained willingly blind.

302
00:23:10.500 --> 00:23:12.750
I'm not taking shit from a mirror.

303
00:23:12.833 --> 00:23:14.333
[distressing. uneasy music playing]

304
00:23:21.708 --> 00:23:27.833
Do you really think that merely averting
the apocalypse you were handmaiden of

305
00:23:27.916 --> 00:23:30.541
can atone for all you've done?

306
00:23:30.625 --> 00:23:33.125
["Afterlife" by Evanescence playing]

307
00:23:33.208 --> 00:23:38.750
<i>♪ Can we just lie here 'til it's all over?</i>
<i>I hear the violence coming. turn and run ♪</i>

308
00:23:41.666 --> 00:23:46.541
[Rabbit. Lady's doppelganger]
I am your masterpiece.

309
00:23:48.625 --> 00:23:51.916
<i>♪ Damned to finally meet you ♪</i>

310
00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:56.500
<i>♪ In the afterlife ♪</i>

311
00:23:56.583 --> 00:24:03.416
♪ <i>Save me from this pain</i>
<i>And fill the hole inside </i>♪

312
00:24:03.500 --> 00:24:10.458
<i>♪ You wonder why</i>
<i>I'm all out of tears to cry ♪</i>

313
00:24:11.166 --> 00:24:13.666
<i>♪ Today I'm not ♪</i>

314
00:24:17.375 --> 00:24:19.416
<i>♪ Not afraid to die ♪</i>

315
00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:21.500
[song trails off]

316
00:24:25.916 --> 00:24:27.083
What was that?

317
00:24:28.541 --> 00:24:30.250
[Vergil] That isn't a mirror.

318
00:24:30.333 --> 00:24:31.375
It's a gateway.

319
00:24:31.458 --> 00:24:32.750
A gateway?

320
00:24:32.833 --> 00:24:34.041
To where?

321
00:24:34.125 --> 00:24:37.041
Arius has ensnared a rare creature here.

322
00:24:37.125 --> 00:24:39.125
A Trismagia.

323
00:24:39.208 --> 00:24:40.750
The oracles of Makai.

324
00:24:42.666 --> 00:24:43.666
Huh?

325
00:24:45.041 --> 00:24:49.250
It's said that their revelations
about their prey are never wrong.

326
00:24:57.500 --> 00:24:58.583
[flies buzzing]

327
00:25:02.083 --> 00:25:05.000
[in Italian] You are my curse!

328
00:25:29.666 --> 00:25:30.666
[heart beating]

329
00:26:21.375 --> 00:26:25.875
[Arius] <i>The first god I met</i>
<i>reeked of whiskey and fear.</i>

330
00:26:31.791 --> 00:26:35.583
<i>In 24 hours. I built a better one.</i>

331
00:26:46.666 --> 00:26:52.291
[sinister voice] We are complete.

332
00:26:52.875 --> 00:26:55.958
After 28 lifetimes.

333
00:26:56.041 --> 00:26:57.250
I…

334
00:26:57.333 --> 00:26:58.416
<i>We…</i>

335
00:26:58.500 --> 00:27:00.125
finally achieved it.

336
00:27:00.208 --> 00:27:02.041
The full Arcana.

337
00:27:02.125 --> 00:27:03.875
At just the right moment.

338
00:27:04.500 --> 00:27:09.416
[sinister voice]
This mortal form will be honored

339
00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:14.791
as the vessel for my rebirth.

340
00:27:15.583 --> 00:27:20.375
We will both be a vessel for a world
released from its shackles.

341
00:27:21.041 --> 00:27:23.000
[sinister voice] Yes.

342
00:27:23.083 --> 00:27:26.833
Liberated by flame.

343
00:27:26.916 --> 00:27:31.375
Every law of nature and civilization

344
00:27:31.458 --> 00:27:34.875
will burn to ash.

345
00:27:35.666 --> 00:27:38.458
We will be

346
00:27:39.041 --> 00:27:41.291
<i>limitless.</i>

347
00:27:45.875 --> 00:27:47.875
[grandiose. operatic music booming]

348
00:28:00.458 --> 00:28:01.750
[Vergil] The Arcana.

349
00:28:12.666 --> 00:28:14.791
Well. well.

350
00:28:14.875 --> 00:28:17.958
The fiercely independent Lady.

351
00:28:18.041 --> 00:28:20.958
who betrayed the brilliant man she served

352
00:28:21.041 --> 00:28:24.250
to serve
her schoolgirl infatuation instead.

353
00:28:25.208 --> 00:28:26.500
How juvenile.

354
00:28:27.666 --> 00:28:32.458
Look. there's no way he gives good enough
benefits for the job to be worth this.

355
00:28:32.541 --> 00:28:35.166
Let's just say you happened
to go on a coffee break.

356
00:28:35.250 --> 00:28:37.041
and we can forget that we ever--

357
00:28:37.125 --> 00:28:38.250
[Dante yelps]

358
00:28:41.208 --> 00:28:43.416
So. it's finally showtime. huh?

359
00:28:43.500 --> 00:28:44.875
Perfect.

360
00:28:51.041 --> 00:28:52.250
Was that…?

361
00:28:52.333 --> 00:28:53.833
An anti-demon bullet.

362
00:28:54.958 --> 00:28:56.791
Judging by appearances.

363
00:28:56.875 --> 00:28:58.458
No. no. no.

364
00:28:58.541 --> 00:29:00.291
A classic mistake.

365
00:29:00.375 --> 00:29:04.083
You think your loud opinions
outweigh quiet observation.

366
00:29:04.166 --> 00:29:06.375
Demon hunter? [chuckles sardonically]

367
00:29:07.375 --> 00:29:11.750
More like an entitled child
playing with matches.

368
00:29:26.166 --> 00:29:28.000
There! Get her!

369
00:29:29.291 --> 00:29:31.208
[frenetic metal rock playing]

370
00:29:33.416 --> 00:29:34.500
Go!

371
00:30:07.416 --> 00:30:11.500
Whatever you are.
you don't have to follow his orders.

372
00:30:11.583 --> 00:30:13.208
You can be better than me.

373
00:30:13.291 --> 00:30:15.666
I <i>am </i>better than you.

374
00:30:31.375 --> 00:30:33.916
- Damn. We need a strategy.
- [Vergil] <i>I </i>have one.

375
00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:36.000
It is you who fights without it.

376
00:30:36.083 --> 00:30:37.500
I mean together.

377
00:30:37.583 --> 00:30:39.916
Remember that time
we played capture the flag?

378
00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:42.166
When the other kids
made us be our own team?

379
00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:43.625
All of them against us.

380
00:30:43.708 --> 00:30:46.541
I remember you knocked over a tree
and almost killed one of them.

381
00:30:46.625 --> 00:30:48.416
Had to blame it
on a freak lightning strike.

382
00:30:48.500 --> 00:30:50.666
Huh. I don't remember that part.

383
00:30:51.166 --> 00:30:52.708
But you know how we got the flag?

384
00:30:54.958 --> 00:30:56.958
[dark. sweeping electro-metal playing]

385
00:31:53.875 --> 00:31:57.000
Clones. They're fucking clones.

386
00:32:01.291 --> 00:32:02.583
Attack!

387
00:32:16.041 --> 00:32:18.125
The children's game is over.

388
00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:35.750
[taut. determined music pulsing]

389
00:32:47.666 --> 00:32:50.458
[Arius] Not only more pretentious than me.

390
00:32:50.958 --> 00:32:52.916
but more hubris as well.

391
00:32:53.000 --> 00:32:56.750
You lost on your own last time
when it was only us.

392
00:32:58.208 --> 00:33:00.291
I still have both my arms.

393
00:33:00.375 --> 00:33:01.666
[growls]

394
00:33:06.416 --> 00:33:09.166
That's the true lesson of Chaos.

395
00:33:09.250 --> 00:33:10.500
Adaptation.

396
00:33:13.583 --> 00:33:17.833
And also. rules are boring.

397
00:33:35.750 --> 00:33:38.458
Why do you insist

398
00:33:38.541 --> 00:33:40.791
on remaining Mundus' slave?

399
00:33:40.875 --> 00:33:44.333
Is it just for the approval
your real father wasn't there to give you?

400
00:33:50.583 --> 00:33:52.916
[Vergil] If you think
you can turn me against him.

401
00:33:53.666 --> 00:33:55.833
you are mistaken.

402
00:33:55.916 --> 00:33:56.916
[resounding clang]

403
00:34:00.750 --> 00:34:02.000
In that case…

404
00:34:23.916 --> 00:34:26.125
[brakes screeching. muffled]

405
00:34:26.208 --> 00:34:28.208
["My Immortal" by Evanescence playing]

406
00:34:28.291 --> 00:34:30.125
[emotional symphonic rock playing]

407
00:34:33.166 --> 00:34:39.875
<i>♪ You used to captivate me</i>
<i>By your resonating light ♪</i>

408
00:34:39.958 --> 00:34:44.291
<i>♪ Now I'm bound</i>
<i>By the life you left behind ♪</i>

409
00:34:44.375 --> 00:34:45.375
[Lady] That was it.

410
00:34:46.500 --> 00:34:49.166
My one fucking chance to redeem myself.

411
00:34:50.416 --> 00:34:52.375
I failed. Again.

412
00:34:52.458 --> 00:34:59.416
<i>♪ Your voice. it chased away</i>
<i>All the sanity in me ♪</i>

413
00:34:59.500 --> 00:35:02.333
<i>♪ These wounds won't seem to heal ♪</i>

414
00:35:02.416 --> 00:35:05.500
<i>♪ This pain is just too real ♪</i>

415
00:35:05.583 --> 00:35:08.000
<i>♪ There's just too much</i>
<i>That time cannot erase ♪</i>

416
00:35:08.083 --> 00:35:09.083
No.

417
00:35:10.125 --> 00:35:10.958
You didn't.

418
00:35:11.708 --> 00:35:17.875
<i>♪ When you cried</i>
<i>I'd wipe away all of your tears ♪</i>

419
00:35:17.958 --> 00:35:24.166
<i>♪ When you'd scream</i>
<i>I'd fight away all of your fears ♪</i>

420
00:35:24.250 --> 00:35:30.708
<i>♪ And I held your hand</i>
<i>Through all of these years ♪</i>

421
00:35:30.791 --> 00:35:36.291
<i>♪ But you still have ♪</i>

422
00:35:38.250 --> 00:35:40.708
<i>♪ All of me ♪</i>

423
00:35:40.791 --> 00:35:42.541
<i>♪ I've tried so hard ♪</i>

424
00:35:43.125 --> 00:35:45.000
[distorted. slowed-down] Jackpot!

425
00:35:45.083 --> 00:35:50.208
<i>♪ To tell myself that you're gone ♪</i>

426
00:35:50.291 --> 00:35:51.916
[barely restrained seething]

427
00:35:53.166 --> 00:35:56.500
[Arius snarling]

428
00:35:56.583 --> 00:35:58.416
You wanted to protect people.

429
00:35:58.500 --> 00:36:00.166
Now we can do it together.

430
00:36:00.250 --> 00:36:05.000
<i>♪ I've been alone all along ♪</i>

431
00:36:05.083 --> 00:36:07.083
[emotional. soaring guitar solo]

432
00:36:18.916 --> 00:36:25.125
<i>♪ When you cried</i>
<i>I'd wipe away all of your tears ♪</i>

433
00:36:25.208 --> 00:36:31.208
<i>♪ When you'd scream</i>
<i>I'd fight away all of your fears ♪</i>

434
00:36:31.291 --> 00:36:37.833
<i>♪ And I held your hand</i>
<i>Through all of these years ♪</i>

435
00:36:37.916 --> 00:36:44.375
<i>♪ But you still have ♪</i>

436
00:36:44.458 --> 00:36:50.666
<i>♪ When you cried</i>
<i>I'd wipe away all of your tears ♪</i>

437
00:36:50.750 --> 00:36:57.166
<i>♪ And I held your hand</i>
<i>Through all of these years ♪</i>

438
00:36:57.250 --> 00:37:02.583
<i>♪ But you still have ♪</i>

439
00:37:05.125 --> 00:37:10.708
<i>♪ All of me </i>♪

440
00:37:13.625 --> 00:37:17.750
<i>♪ Me ♪</i>

441
00:37:20.500 --> 00:37:24.875
<i>♪ Me ♪</i>

442
00:37:33.875 --> 00:37:35.875
["My Immortal" trailing off]

443
00:37:36.305 --> 00:38:36.399
